    <p>Mr. Marx is here portrayed as the interlocutor his finest arguments deserve &mdash; engaged, exacting, and
      ultimately willing to concede what is true. The debate occasionally grows heated; it never grows dishonest.
      The two men find, at the evening&rsquo;s close, that they agree on more than either predicted.</p>
    <p class="version-note"><em>The debate as one might wish it had gone.</em></p>
